GrasshopperScriptModel.ChainOfThought: To create a cup shape in Grasshopper, we'll first create a circle using a 'Circle CNR' component, which will act as the base of the cup. Then, we will use a 'Move' component to move the base circle vertically to create the upper rim of the cup. To create the body of the cup, we'll loft these two circles using a 'Loft' component.
GrasshopperScriptModel.Advice: Remember, to properly define the cups dimensions using the number slider
